President Obama has issued a statement expressing his gratitude for the Senate confirmation of Ambassador Mari Carmen Aponte. The President praises Ambassador Aponte for her effective advocacy for the United States in El Salvador, earning respect from various sectors. He highlights her efforts in advancing citizen security and combating transnational crime. The President also acknowledges Ambassador Aponte's commitment to democratic governance in the region. He expresses his appreciation for her service and recognizes the hard work of Majority Leader Harry Reid and Senator Robert Menendez in achieving her confirmation. The President emphasizes the importance of perseverance and the need for national security to transcend politics. He looks forward to continuing to work with Ambassador Aponte to strengthen partnerships with El Salvador and other countries in the Americas.